'''Checkpoint Strikeforce''' is a multi-jurisdictional program in [[Virginia]], [[Washington DC]], [[Delaware]], [[West Virginia]], and [[Maryland]] to combat [[drunk driving]]. Its motto is "Drunk driving, over the limit, under arrest." Checkpoint Strikeforce began in Virginia in 2002.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.governor.virginia.gov/news/viewRelease.cfm?id=2010# |title=Governor McDonnell Highlights 2013 Checkpoint Strikeforce Campaign |access-date=2013-12-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131215101936/http://www.governor.virginia.gov/news/viewRelease.cfm?id=2010# |archive-date=2013-12-15 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> In 2007, 800,000 drivers were stopped at Checkpoint Strikeforce sobriety checkpoints.<ref>[http://www.virginia-criminallawyer.com/dui/fairfax-dui-checkpoints DUI Checkpoints]</ref>
==Campaigns== In 2013,<ref>[http://smnewsnet.com/archives/84947 “Thanksgiving Belts & Booze” Campaign to Focus on Impaired Driving and Seatbelt Enforcement]</ref> jurisdictions took part in the "Thanksgiving Belts & Booze Campaign" to draw attention to the high rate of DUI crashes that occur over the holidays.<ref>[http://news.delaware.gov/2013/11/12/dui-checkpoints-continue-in-november/ DUI Checkpoints Continue In November]</ref> The campaign lasted from November 25 to December 13, 2013.<ref>[http://smnewsnet.com/archives/86161 Sobriety Checkpoint: Three Notch Road in the Hollywood Area]</ref>
