{{no footnotes|date = January 2012}}

An '''Internationale Bauausstellung''' ('''IBA''') or International Architecture Exhibition is a [[Germany|German]] tool for [[urban engineering]] and [[architecture]], in order to show new concepts in terms of social, cultural and ecologic ideas.

== History ==
* The first one dates to 1901 and was held in [[Darmstadt]].
* [[Interbau|IBA '57 ]] was organised in Berlin.
* 1979-87 [[International Building Exhibition Berlin|IBA Berlin]] was an urban renewal project which followed the strategies of "careful urban renewal" and "[[critical reconstruction]]". The program inspired the formation of the group [[Feministische Organisation von Planerinnen und Architektinnen]] (Feminist Architects and Planners Organisation or FOPA), who objected to its failure to adequately address women-specific issues and involve female designers. 
* 1989-99 [[Internationale Bauausstellung Emscher Park|IBA Emscher Park]] aimed at restructuring a former industrial region, the [[Ruhr]], by sparking urbanistic, architectural, cultural, and economic incentives.<ref>{{cite web|title=Brief English Info IBA Emscher Park|url=http://www.iba-emscherpark.de/pageID_2507086.html}}</ref>

== Current ==
* 2012-20 [[International Building Exhibition Parkstad|IBA Parkstad]] is the first IBA to be held completely outsite of Germany, in the former mining region of [[Parkstad Limburg]] in the [[Netherlands]]. Currently at least 39 projects have been chosen to develop further.<ref>{{cite web|title=Official website of IBA Parkstad|url=http://www.iba-parkstad.nl/en}}</ref>

