This is a '''list of notable people assassinated by the [[Janatha Vimukthi Peramuna]]''' (JVP). JVP is a Sri Lankan [[Marxist-Leninist]], [[communist]] party which was involved in two armed uprisings against the ruling governments in 1971 (SLFP) and 1987–89 (UNP). Later it entered democratic politics by participating in the [[Sri Lankan parliamentary election, 1994|1994 parliamentary election]].
==1971 JVP Insurrection== * [[Rex De Costa]]<ref>[http://archives.dailynews.lk/2011/05/07/fea50.asp Doctor, planter, soldier and patriot]-Colonel Dr.Ranjana W. Seneviratne,Daily news (Saturday, 7 May 2011)</ref> - Former [[commanding officer]] of the Ruhunu Regiment and a [[medical doctor]] in the [[Ceylon Defence Force]] during [[World War II]], former Vice President of the World Veterans Federation * [[Noel Weerakoon]], [[Ceylon Artillery|CA]]<ref>[http://www.island.lk/2007/04/15/politics5.html Counter Insurgency Operations - Wellawaya April 1971]</ref> - [[Royal Military Academy Sandhurst|RMA Sandhurst]] and [[Ceylon Army]] cricketer
==1987–89 JVP Insurrection== {{Main|List of assassinations of the Second JVP Insurrection}}
* [[Amara Wellappuli]]<ref name=o/> - Attorney-At-Law * [[Anura Daniel]]<ref name=llib/> - United National Party MP for [[Kandy]] * [[Chandratne Patuwathavithane]]<ref name="jvp">{{cite web | url=http://www.thesundayleader.lk/archive/20080210/issues.htm | title=JVP's double take on the 13th Amendment | publisher=Sunday Leader | date=Feb 10, 2008 | accessdate=11 April 2014 | author=Dilrukshi Handunnetti and Ranjith Jayasundera}}</ref> - Academic & Former vice chancellor of [[University of Moratuwa]] * [[D. C. Atukorala]]<ref name=o/> - A Chief Engineer attached to the Ports Authority, Sri Lanka * [[Assassination of Daya Pathirana|Daya Pathirana]]<ref name="san">{{cite web | url=http://www.sangam.org/taraki/articles/2006/01-25_JVP_and_Pol_Potism.php?uid=1462 | title=The JVP and 'Pol Potism' | publisher=Sanagam.org | date=January 25, 2006 | accessdate=11 April 2014 | author=Jayatilleke, Dayan}}</ref> - Former leader of the [[Independent Students Union]] (ISU) of University of Colombo * [[Daya Sepali Senadhira]]<ref name="jvp" /> - United National Party MP for Karandeniya * [[Deputy inspector general of police|DIG]] [[Bennet Perera]]<ref name=Hm/> - Former Director [[Criminal Investigation Department (Sri Lanka)|Criminal Investigation Department]] of Sri Lanka. * [[Deputy inspector general of police|DIG]] [[Terrance Perera]]<ref name=Hm>[http://www.thesundayleader.lk/archive/20040321/spotlight.htm Haunting memories of the JVP that linger], Sunday Leader</ref> - Former director of the counter subversive division, [[Sri Lanka Police]] * [[Esmie Amarasiri]]<ref name=o/> - Wife of [[M. S. Amarasiri]], former Chief Minister, Southern Provincial Council, Sri Lanka * [[G. V. S. de Silva]]<ref name=llib/> - Former district minister and United National Party MP for [[Habaraduwa]] * [[Gamini Medagedera]]<ref name=sl/> - attorney at law, english teacher and secretary of sri lanka communist party polonnaruwa * [[Gladys Jayawardene]]<ref name=so>[http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2013/05/19/pol04.asp Yes, we killed], Sunday Observer</ref> - Former Chairman of State Pharmaceutical Corporation of Sri Lanka. * [[Harsha Abeywardena]]<ref name=sl>[http://www.thesundayleader.lk/archive/20080210/issues.htm JVP's double take on the 13th Amendment], The Sunday Leader</ref> - Former chairman of the [[United National Party]] * [[Jinadasa Weerasinghe]]<ref name=llib>[http://www.lankalibrary.com/pol/jvp2.htm Haunting memories of the JVP that linger], Fedrica Janz, Lanka Library</ref> - United National Party MP for [[Tangalle]] * [[K. Amaratunge]]<ref name=o>[http://www.island.lk/2004/03/27/opinio01.html Wolf in a sheep’s skin – JVP’s new clothes], The Island</ref> - Chief News Editor, [[Sri Lanka Rupavahini Corporation]] * [[L. W. Panditha]]<ref name=sl/> - Member of Sri Lankan communist Party and Trade unionist * [[Lesley Ranagala]]<ref name="jvp" /> - United National Party MP for [[Borella]] * [[Leslie Yatanwala]]<ref name=o/> - Attorney-At-Law * [[Lionel Jayatilake]]<ref name=llib/> - Former minister and United National Party MP * [[Merrill Kariyawasam]]<ref name="jvp" /> - United National Party MP for [[Agalawatte]] * [[Nandalal Fernando]]<ref>[http://archives.dailynews.lk/2010/03/13/fea03.asp JVP assassination of Nandalal Fernando:JVP fear psychosis - Part VI], Daily News, Geoff Wijesinghe </ref> Former General Secretary of United National Party * [[Premakeerthi de Alwis]]<ref name="aw">{{cite web | url=http://archives.dailynews.lk/2010/07/31/fea02.asp | title=Premakeerthi de Alwis and colours that remain unnamed | publisher=Daily News | date=31 July 2010 | accessdate=11 March 2014 | author=Seneviratne, Malinda}}</ref>- Famous Sri Lankan radio and television broadcaster and lyricist. * Rev. Fr. [[Michael Paul Rodrigo]], OMI<ref name=o/><ref>[http://archives.dailynews.lk/2008/11/13/fea12.asp Christian Perspectives], Daily News</ref> - Catholic priest * [[Sagarika Gomes]]<ref>[http://archives.dailynews.lk/2008/12/10/fea03.asp The JVP and LTTE are two of a kind], Daily News Goshaka</ref> - Artist and TV newscaster. * [[Stanley Wijesundera]]<ref name="jvp" /> - Sri Lankan academic and a Professor of Chemistry, the first Vice Chancellor of the [[University of Colombo]] and former the Chairman of the [[Association of Commonwealth Universities]] * [[Thevis Guruge]]<ref name="jvp" /> - Distinguished broadcaster with [[Radio Ceylon]] and subsequently the [[Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation]]. First Sinhala Announcer of the Radio Ceylon * Ven. [[Kotikawatte Saddhatissa Thera]]<ref name=so/> - Famous Buddhist monk * Ven. [[Pohaddaramulle Premaloka Thero]]<ref name=sl/> - Buddhist monk * [[Vijaya Kumaranatunga]]<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/sinhala/news/story/2008/02/080219_chandrika_vijaya.shtml Devolution only solution - CBK ] - Saroj Pathirana, BBC Sinhala Service</ref>{{Efn|Other sources blame Kumaranatunga's assassination on the [[Government of Sri Lanka|Government]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vijaya Kumaratunga assassination was a UNP conspiracy|url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2004/03/21/new03.html|work=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)]]|date=21 March 2004|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924112040/http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2004/03/21/new03.html|archivedate=24 September 2015|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Seneviratne|first1=Tassie|title=Vijaya assassination: Politics kills police professionalism|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/120212/News/nws_28.html|work=[[The Sunday Times (Sri Lanka)]]|date=12 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Rajasingham|first=K. T.|title=Sri Lanka: The Untold Story|url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/South_Asia/DI28Df01.html|chapter=Chapter 59: Queries over Premadasa's slaying}}</ref>}} - Popular Sri Lankan film actor and politician, founder of [[Sri Lanka Mahajana Party]] (SLMP) * [[W. M. G. T. Banda]]<ref name="jvp" /> - Former Minister of Buddhist Affairs and United National Party MP for Galagedara
