[[Image:WCSS2006.jpg|thumb|right|'''World Congress of Soil Science''' held in [[Philadelphia]], [[United States|U.S.]] in 2006]]
The '''World Congress of Soil Science''' (WCSS) is a conference held every four years (although interrupted by [[World War II]]) under the guidance of the [[International Union of Soil Sciences]] (IUSS). The purpose of a congress is to: (i) ensure the advancement of [[soil science]] and its application, and (ii) to handle the business of the society. Of the 18 congresses, eight have been held in Europe, five in the Americas, three in Asia, one in Australia and one in Africa. The congresses are only open to society members. The number of members attending has steadily increased, with approximately 2000 members attending each congress since the 15th WCSS in [[Acapulco]], [[Mexico]].<ref name="van Baren et al 2000">{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/S0016-7061(99)00097-X |title=75 years the International Society of Soil Science |journal=Geoderma |volume=96 |pages=1–18 |year=2000 |last1=Van Baren |first1=Hans |last2=Hartemink |first2=A.E |last3=Tinker |first3=P.B |bibcode=2000Geode..96....1V }}</ref>
The 19th WCSS was held in the week of 1 to 6 August 2010<ref name="iuss.org">[http://www.iuss.org/bull110files/19thwcss.htm International Union of Soil Sciences<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> in [[Brisbane]], [[Queensland]], [[Australia]] at the [[Brisbane Convention and Exhibition Centre]]. The congress theme was ”''Soil solutions for a changing world''”.<ref name="iuss.org"/> The conference was organised by the IUSS President ([[Roger Swift]]) and Vice-President ([[Neal Menzies]]).<ref>[http://www.iuss.org/bull104files/presidentelect.htm IUSS Bulletin 104 (June 2004)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The 19th WCSS was the second congress held in Australia (the 9th WCSS was held in [[Adelaide]], [[Australia]], in 1968), and was held in conjunction with the [[Australian Society of Soil Science Incorporated]]. The 20th WCSS was held from 8 to 13 June 2014 on [[Jeju-do]] Island, [[South Korea]] The 21st WCSS was held in [[Rio de Janeiro]]<ref>[https://www.21wcss.org/index.php Rio de Janeiro 2018]</ref> ([[Brazil]]) in August 2018. The upcoming WCSS are 2022 in [[Glasgow]]<ref>[https://www.soils.org.uk/wcss2022 Glasgow 2022]</ref> ([[Scotland]], [[United Kingdom]]) and 2026 in [[Nanjing]] ([[China]]).
Past and future locations for the WCSS:<ref name="van Baren et al 2000"/><ref>[http://www.iuss.org/pages/congress.htm IUSS Congresses<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070404111656/http://www.iuss.org/pages/congress.htm |date=2007-04-04 }}</ref>
